text: is a Japanese cable and satellite television channel operated by Turner Japan. ==Programming== The channel is aimed at children. It mostly airs animated television series. As a Japanese version of the eponymous television channel in the United States, Cartoon Network broadcasts original series from its U.S. counterpart, as well as several Japanese animated series and films, and other non-Japanese programs. === Current Cartoonito programming === * Clifford the Big Red Dog (2019) でっかくなっちゃった赤い子犬 僕はクリフォード * Bunsen is a Beast ブンゼンは野獣 * TMNT ティーンエイジ・ミュータント・ニンジャ・タートルズ * Dora the Explorer ドーラ・ザ・エクスプローラー * Team Umizoomi チームうみぞーみ * Miffy's Adventures Big and Small ミッフィーの冒険 大小 * 64 Zoo Lane 64 ズーレーン * Pingu ピングー * Hey Duggee ヘイ・ダギー * Little Charley Bear リトル チャーリー ベア * Dragon ドラゴン * Driver Dan's Story Train ドライバーダンのストーリートレイン * Guess with Jess ジェスと推測する * Zigby ジグビー * Dinosaur Train 恐竜列車 * Little Bill リトル・ビル * Lego Friends レゴフレンズ * Peg + Cat ペグ+ネコ * Go Jetters ゴー、ジェッターズ * Big & Small 大きな小 ==History== On October 1, 2011, Cartoon Network in Japan & English, along with other versions of Cartoon Network operated by Turner Broadcasting System Asia Pacific, adopted its current branding. On April 1, 2017, the channel started using graphics from Cartoon Network USA's Dimensional brand package. On January 1, 2022, the channel started using graphics from Cartoon Network USA's Redraw Your World brand package. == References == == Other websites == * Category:Television stations Category:Cartoon Network Category:1997 establishments in Japan
